def: One who directs; a director. Directer plane (Geom.), the planeto which all right-lined elements in a warped surface are parallel.
Of or pertaining to the spleen; lienal; as, the splenic vein.Splenic apoplexy or fever. (Med.) See Anthrax, n., 3.

The quality of being incomprehensible, or beyond the reach ofhuman intellect; incomprehensibleness; inconceivability;inexplicability.The constant, universal sense of all antiquity unanimously confessingan incomprehensibility in many of the articles of the Christianfaith. South.
Joined as a companion; brought into association; accompanying;combined. Associated movements (Physiol.), consensual movements whichaccompany voluntary efforts without our consciousness. Dunglison.

A violent and peremptory procedure without any assigned reason;a sudden conclusive happening. [Obs.]When the church Was taken with a why-not in the lurch. Hudibras.This game . . . was like to have been lost with a why-not. NugæAntiq.
Having the shape of an isopod; -- said of the larvæ of certaininsects.
One whose occupation is to dye cloth and the like. Dyer'sbroom, Dyer's rocket, Dyer's weed. See Dyer's broom, under Broom.

Of or pertaining to electrical tension; -- said of a supposedpeculiar condition of a conducting circuit during its exposure to theaction of another conducting circuit traversed by a uniform electriccurrent when both circuits remain stationary. Faraday.
A genus of Lower Silurian trilobites in which the glabella andcheeks form three rounded elevations on the head.
The quality or state of being verbose; the use of more wordsthan are necessary; prolixity; wordiness; verbiage.The worst fault, by far, is the extreme diffuseness and verbosity ofhis style. Jeffrey.
The state of being incommoded; inconvenience. [Obs.]
